## Shopping Blue Nile Bezel Settings for Pear Diamonds

**The baguette three-stone family ($3,030–$3,325)** is the entry point for bezel pear settings on Blue Nile. Three variations — yellow gold, rose gold, white gold — are priced identically at $3,030. Platinum adds $295. The baguette side stones create a strict, architectural look: three stones, three bezels, a linear arrangement. The pear center's curvature contrasts with the baguette sides' flat ends. This is a strong combination for buyers who want the modern bezel aesthetic without the design complexity of emerald side stones.

The two reviews on the baguette three-stone settings are meaningful data in a category where most settings have no reviews. Two reviews are enough to confirm that the setting works as described — that it accepts pear center stones cleanly, that the bezel closes correctly, and that the finished ring looks as photographed. In the bezel pear category where The Bezel Shoulder Rule violations are a real risk, confirmed reviews from buyers who received and wore the ring are more valuable than a setting description alone.

**The channel-set accent family ($3,600–$4,500)** is for buyers who want bezel architecture without the formality of a three-stone design. The channel-set accent setting adds small pavé or channel diamonds running down the band from the bezel head, creating a sparkling transition between the center stone and the plain shank. This setting family is available in all four metals with a $900 jump from 14K to platinum. No reviews are listed on these settings at present — shop with the understanding that you are purchasing based on Blue Nile's standard quality guarantee rather than buyer-confirmed performance.

**The emerald side stone family ($4,300–$5,260)** pairs a pear center with emerald-cut side stones, all in individual bezel collets. This is the most sophisticated of the three setting families — three distinct stone shapes, three distinct bezel frames, all in a linear arrangement. The result reads as architectural, almost Art Deco in character. The emerald side stones' rectangular profiles and step-cut facets contrast with the pear's brilliant-cut sparkle, creating a deliberate tension between the stones. One review per metal variant confirms the setting ships and performs as described.

